# No void operator in handlers

Sonar rule: remove unnecessary `void` in callbacks.

**Sync handler** (returns void):

```tsx
// Bad
onClick={() => void onExport(wf)}

// Good
onClick={() => onExport(wf)}
```

**Async handler** (returns Promise):

```tsx
// Bad
onClick={() => void onDelete(id)}

// Good
onClick={() => {
  void onDelete(id).catch(() => {});
}}
// Or define: const handleDelete = () => { void onDelete(id); }; — prefer explicit .catch for Sonar
```

Use `node scripts/sonar/fix-void-operator.mjs --files=path/to/file.tsx` for mechanical batches.
